# Shadow DOM CSS Architecture

## Rule: Never use @scope CSS

CSS isolation is handled by Shadow DOM. Never generate `@scope` CSS in any context.
`_wrapCssInScope` and `renderCustomCSS` in libs/monkey.js are DEPRECATED — do not call or extend them.

## Shadow DOM CSS injection (`getCustomCssTagsForShadowDom`)

- External CSS URLs (from profile `external_css_links`): inject as `<link rel="stylesheet">` inside the shadow `<head>`. Do NOT fetch these client-side.
- Inline CSS (from profile `customizations.css`): strip scope via `_stripEditorContentScopeForShadowDom`, then put in `<style>` inside the shadow.
- Do NOT use `_getRawCombinedCustomCss` for shadow DOM path.

## Font loading (main document head)

When getCustomCssTagsForShadowDom runs, any external CSS URL from the user profile that matches
FONT_CDN_WHITELIST is duplicated into document.head as `<link rel="stylesheet" data-custom-css-font-link>`.
This primes the browser font cache so shadow DOM fonts load correctly.
Do NOT use _extractRootRules, _injectRootRulesIntoDocumentHead, _getPreloadFontUrlsForExternalCssLinks,
or _ensurePreloadLinksInDocumentHead — all are deprecated and unused.
